A. Anti-IGF-1-Coated Microttitration Strips: One stripholder containing 96 microtitration wells coated with anti-IGF-1 antibody.
B. IGF-1 Standard A/Sample Diluent: containing 0 ng/ml IGF-1 in protein-based (BSA) buffer with a non-mercury preservative.
C. IGF-1 Standard B-F: containing concentrations of approximately 10, 50, 140, 300, and 600 ng/ml IGF-1 (synthetic) in a protein-based (BSA) buffer with a non-mercury preservative.
D. IGF-1 Controls: containing low and high concentrations of IGF-1 in a protein-based (BSA) buffer with non-mercury preservative.
E. Assay Buffer B: containing a protein-based (BSA) buffer with a non-mercury preservative.
F. IGF-1 Antibody-Enzyme Conjugate Concentrate: containing anti-IGF-1 antibody conjugated to the enzyme horseradish peroxidase in a protein-based (BSA) buffer with a non-mercury preservative.
G. TMB Chromogen Solution: containing a solution of tetramethylbenzidine (TMB) in buffer with hydrogen peroxide.
